{"title":"Fishing","markdown":{"yaml":{"title":"Fishing","author":"Gorton, Bec (Environment, Hobart)"},"headingText":"Imposed Catch","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\n\nThis is used when the flagimposecatch_ value for the given fishery/species is not 0.  \nThe following options are supported:\n\n1 - Global   \n2 - Spatially Explicit  \n3 - Stock associated  \n4 - Adjacent cells\n\nThe fishing catch values are read in from provided TS files.\n\n### Fishing Mortality\n\nThis is used when flagF is true for the fishery/species.\n\nFished Biomass = mFC * mFC_brokenStick_scale * mpa_scale * mFC_scale * Biomass\n\n**mFC_brokenStick_scale**\n\nApply any broken stick scaling. This scaler is calculated at the start of each year based on the fishing levels from the previous year.\n\n**mpa_scale**  \nWhere MPA_scale is set to the MPA status of the current cell if '_flagmpa' is set to 1 for that fishery.\n\n**mFC_scale**  \nIf the 'flagchangeF' value is set to true in the input file then the fishing mortality values can change over time. This scaling is then controlled using the following values:\n\n'_mFC_changes' - The number of changes in mFC for the group over each fishery.  \n'mFCchange_start_' - The day from the run start that the mFC change starts.  \n'mFCchange_period_' - The period over which the change occurs.  \n'mFCchange_mult_' - The multiplication factor applied.\n\n### Dynamic Catch\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":"\n\n### Imposed Catch\n\nThis is used when the flagimposecatch_ value for the given fishery/species is not 0.  \nThe following options are supported:\n\n1 - Global   \n2 - Spatially Explicit  \n3 - Stock associated  \n4 - Adjacent cells\n\nThe fishing catch values are read in from provided TS files.\n\n### Fishing Mortality\n\nThis is used when flagF is true for the fishery/species.\n\nFished Biomass = mFC * mFC_brokenStick_scale * mpa_scale * mFC_scale * Biomass\n\n**mFC_brokenStick_scale**\n\nApply any broken stick scaling. This scaler is calculated at the start of each year based on the fishing levels from the previous year.\n\n**mpa_scale**  \nWhere MPA_scale is set to the MPA status of the current cell if '_flagmpa' is set to 1 for that fishery.\n\n**mFC_scale**  \nIf the 'flagchangeF' value is set to true in the input file then the fishing mortality values can change over time. This scaling is then controlled using the following values:\n\n'_mFC_changes' - The number of changes in mFC for the group over each fishery.  \n'mFCchange_start_' - The day from the run start that the mFC change starts.  \n'mFCchange_period_' - The period over which the change occurs.  \n'mFCchange_mult_' - The multiplication factor applied.\n\n### Dynamic Catch\n"},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":"auto","echo":true,"output":true,"warning":true,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":null,"daemon":null,"daemon-restart":false,"debug":false,"ipynb-filters":[],"ipynb-shell-interactivity":null,"plotly-connected":true,"engine":"markdown"},"render":{"keep-tex":false,"keep-typ":false,"keep-source":false,"keep-hidden":false,"prefer-html":false,"output-divs":true,"output-ext":"html","fig-align":"default","fig-pos":null,"fig-env":null,"code-fold":"none","code-overflow":"wrap","code-link":false,"code-line-numbers":false,"code-tools":false,"tbl-colwidths":"auto","merge-includes":true,"inline-includes":false,"preserve-yaml":false,"latex-auto-mk":true,"latex-auto-install":true,"latex-clean":true,"latex-min-runs":1,"latex-max-runs":10,"latex-makeindex":"makeindex","latex-makeindex-opts":[],"latex-tlmgr-opts":[],"latex-input-paths":[],"latex-output-dir":null,"link-external-icon":false,"link-external-newwindow":false,"self-contained-math":false,"format-resources":[],"notebook-links":true},"pandoc":{"standalone":true,